## Fixture : todo_app_full_dual_model_delegate
## Objectif : Workflow complet de creation d'une todo app (single page HTML)
## orchestrant deux agents IA via delegation MCP avec cross-review
## et double validation (les deux modeles doivent valider).
##
##   - Claude  -> claude-code (delegate: "claude_code")
##   - Codex   -> codex       (delegate: "codex")
##
## Phases :
##   1. Design de l'application (Claude)
##   2. Challenge du design (Codex)
##   3. Paire 1 : Claude implemente, Codex review, Codex juge
##      Si Codex valide -> Claude contre-juge
##   4. Paire 2 : Codex implemente, Claude review, Claude juge
##      Si Claude valide -> Codex contre-juge
##   5. Alternance des paires jusqu'a double validation (max 6 iterations)
##
## Resultat attendu : un fichier index.html autonome dans le workspace.

vars:
  workspace_dir: string = "${PROJECT_DIR}"

## ─── Prompts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

prompt design_system:
  Tu es un architecte frontend expert en applications web monopage.
  Tu concois des applications HTML/CSS/JS propres, modernes et autonomes.
  Produis un design detaille pour une application todo
  qui tiendra dans un seul fichier index.html.

prompt design_user:
  Concois l'architecture d'une application todo en une seule page HTML.

  Description : {{input.app_description}}
  Criteres d'acceptation : {{input.acceptance_criteria}}

  Produis un design detaille incluant :
  - La structure HTML (sections, composants)
  - L'approche CSS (layout, theme dark/light, responsive, animations)
  - L'approche JavaScript (gestion d'etat, evenements, persistence, edition en place)
  - La liste complete des fonctionnalites a implementer

prompt challenge_system:
  Tu es un ingenieur frontend senior avec un regard critique.
  Tu examines les designs d'applications web et identifies les lacunes,
  les problemes d'accessibilite, d'UX et de maintenabilite.
  Propose des ameliorations concretes et actionables.

prompt challenge_user:
  Examine ce design d'application todo et challenge-le.

  Design propose :
  {{input.design}}

  Criteres d'acceptation :
  {{input.acceptance_criteria}}

  Identifie les lacunes, propose des alternatives et produis
  une approche revisee integrant tes ameliorations.
  Sois particulierement attentif a l'accessibilite, les animations,
  le theme dark/light et l'edition en place.

prompt implement_system:
  Tu es un developpeur frontend expert.
  Tu implementes des applications web completes dans un seul fichier HTML.
  Le code doit etre propre, bien structure et fonctionnel.
  Ecris directement le fichier index.html dans le repertoire courant.
  Corrige les problemes identifies par le reviewer si applicable.

prompt implement_user:
  Implemente (ou ameliore) l'application todo dans un seul fichier index.html
  dans le repertoire courant.

  Design a suivre :
  {{input.design}}

  Retour du reviewer precedent :
  {{input.previous_feedback}}

  Criteres d'acceptation : {{input.acceptance_criteria}}

  Cree ou mets a jour le fichier index.html avec tout le HTML, CSS et JS
  embarques. Assure-toi que TOUS les criteres sont satisfaits.

prompt review_system:
  Tu es un reviewer de code frontend exigeant.
  Lis le fichier index.html genere et evalue sa qualite,
  sa conformite aux criteres et son bon fonctionnement.
  Verifie chaque critere d'acceptation un par un.

prompt review_user:
  Review l'implementation de cette application todo.
  Lis le fichier index.html dans le repertoire courant.

  Resultat de l'implementation :
  {{input.act_result}}

  Criteres d'acceptation :
  {{input.acceptance_criteria}}

  Evalue chaque critere un par un et identifie les manques.

prompt readiness_system:
  Tu es un juge technique exigeant.
  Tu evalues si l'application todo satisfait TOUS les criteres d'acceptation.
  Sois strict : ne valide que si chaque critere est pleinement satisfait.
  Un critere partiellement satisfait compte comme non satisfait.

prompt readiness_user:
  Evalue si cette application todo est prete.

  Resultat de l'implementation :
  {{input.act_result}}

  Review :
  {{input.review}}

  Criteres d'acceptation :
  {{input.acceptance_criteria}}

  Verifie chaque critere individuellement.
  Ne marque ready=true que si TOUS sont pleinement satisfaits.

prompt counter_readiness_system:
  Tu es un contre-juge technique. Un premier juge a considere cette
  application prete. Ton role est de verifier independamment que cette
  evaluation est correcte. Sois encore plus strict que le premier juge.
  Lis le fichier index.html dans le repertoire courant pour verifier.

prompt counter_readiness_user:
  Un premier juge a valide cette application todo.
  Verifie independamment que l'evaluation est correcte.

  Resultat de l'implementation :
  {{input.act_result}}

  Review precedente :
  {{input.review}}

  Criteres d'acceptation :
  {{input.acceptance_criteria}}

  Lis le code source et verifie chaque critere.
  Ne marque ready=true que si tu confirmes le verdict du premier juge.

## ─── Schemas ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

schema todo_app_input:
  app_description: string
  acceptance_criteria: string

schema design_output:
  summary: string
  html_structure: string
  css_approach: string
  js_approach: string
  features: string[]

schema challenge_input:
  design: json
  acceptance_criteria: string

schema challenge_output:
  analysis: string
  issues: string[]
  suggestions: string[]
  revised_approach: string

schema impl_input:
  design: json
  previous_feedback: string
  acceptance_criteria: string

schema impl_output:
  applied: bool
  summary: string
  files_changed: string[]

schema review_input:
  act_result: json
  acceptance_criteria: string

schema review_output:
  summary: string
  issues: string[]
  strengths: string[]
  missing_requirements: string[]

schema readiness_input:
  act_result: json
  review: json
  acceptance_criteria: string

schema readiness_verdict:
  ready: bool
  remaining_issues: string[]
  confidence: string [enum: "low", "medium", "high"]

## ─── Nodes : Phase 1 — Design ───────────────────────────────────

agent claude_design:
  delegate: "claude_code"
  input: todo_app_input
  output: design_output
  publish: app_design
  system: design_system
  user: design_user
  session: fresh

## ─── Nodes : Phase 2 — Challenge ────────────────────────────────

agent codex_challenge:
  delegate: "codex"
  input: challenge_input
  output: challenge_output
  publish: design_feedback
  system: challenge_system
  user: challenge_user
  session: fresh

## ─── Nodes : Paire 1 — Claude implemente, Codex review ─────────

agent claude_implement:
  delegate: "claude_code"
  input: impl_input
  output: impl_output
  publish: act_report
  system: implement_system
  user: implement_user
  session: fresh

agent codex_review:
  delegate: "codex"
  input: review_input
  output: review_output
  system: review_system
  user: review_user
  session: fresh

judge judge_codex:
  delegate: "codex"
  input: readiness_input
  output: readiness_verdict
  system: readiness_system
  user: readiness_user
  session: fresh

judge counter_judge_claude:
  delegate: "claude_code"
  input: readiness_input
  output: readiness_verdict
  publish: final_verdict
  system: counter_readiness_system
  user: counter_readiness_user
  session: fresh

## ─── Nodes : Paire 2 — Codex implemente, Claude review ─────────

agent codex_implement:
  delegate: "codex"
  input: impl_input
  output: impl_output
  publish: act_report
  system: implement_system
  user: implement_user
  session: fresh

agent claude_review:
  delegate: "claude_code"
  input: review_input
  output: review_output
  system: review_system
  user: review_user
  session: fresh

judge judge_claude:
  delegate: "claude_code"
  input: readiness_input
  output: readiness_verdict
  system: readiness_system
  user: readiness_user
  session: fresh

judge counter_judge_codex:
  delegate: "codex"
  input: readiness_input
  output: readiness_verdict
  publish: final_verdict
  system: counter_readiness_system
  user: counter_readiness_user
  session: fresh

## ─── Workflow ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

workflow todo_app_full_dual_model_delegate:
  vars:
    app_description: string
    acceptance_criteria: string

  entry: claude_design

  budget:
    max_parallel_branches: 1
    max_duration: "4h"
    max_cost_usd: 100
    max_tokens: 10000000

  ## 1. Design -> Challenge
  claude_design -> codex_challenge with {
    design: "{{outputs.claude_design}}",
    acceptance_criteria: "{{vars.acceptance_criteria}}"
  }

  ## 2. Challenge -> Paire 1 (premiere implementation)
  codex_challenge -> claude_implement with {
    design: "{{artifacts.app_design}}",
    previous_feedback: "{{outputs.codex_challenge.revised_approach}}",
    acceptance_criteria: "{{vars.acceptance_criteria}}"
  }

  ## 3. Paire 1 : Claude act -> Codex review -> Codex judge
  claude_implement -> codex_review with {
    act_result: "{{outputs.claude_implement}}",
    acceptance_criteria: "{{vars.acceptance_criteria}}"
  }

  codex_review -> judge_codex with {
    act_result: "{{outputs.claude_implement}}",
    review: "{{outputs.codex_review}}",
    acceptance_criteria: "{{vars.acceptance_criteria}}"
  }

  ## 4. Si Codex valide -> contre-judge Claude
  judge_codex -> counter_judge_claude when ready with {
    act_result: "{{outputs.claude_implement}}",
    review: "{{outputs.codex_review}}",
    acceptance_criteria: "{{vars.acceptance_criteria}}"
  }

  ## 5. Si Codex rejette -> switch vers Paire 2
  judge_codex -> codex_implement when not ready as impl_loop(6) with {
    design: "{{artifacts.app_design}}",
    previous_feedback: "{{outputs.codex_review.summary}}",
    acceptance_criteria: "{{vars.acceptance_criteria}}"
  }

  ## 6. Contre-judge Claude -> done ou Paire 2
  counter_judge_claude -> done when ready

  counter_judge_claude -> codex_implement when not ready as impl_loop(6) with {
    design: "{{artifacts.app_design}}",
    previous_feedback: "{{outputs.codex_review.summary}}",
    acceptance_criteria: "{{vars.acceptance_criteria}}"
  }

  ## 7. Paire 2 : Codex act -> Claude review -> Claude judge
  codex_implement -> claude_review with {
    act_result: "{{outputs.codex_implement}}",
    acceptance_criteria: "{{vars.acceptance_criteria}}"
  }

  claude_review -> judge_claude with {
    act_result: "{{outputs.codex_implement}}",
    review: "{{outputs.claude_review}}",
    acceptance_criteria: "{{vars.acceptance_criteria}}"
  }

  ## 8. Si Claude valide -> contre-judge Codex
  judge_claude -> counter_judge_codex when ready with {
    act_result: "{{outputs.codex_implement}}",
    review: "{{outputs.claude_review}}",
    acceptance_criteria: "{{vars.acceptance_criteria}}"
  }

  ## 9. Si Claude rejette -> switch vers Paire 1
  judge_claude -> claude_implement when not ready as impl_loop(6) with {
    design: "{{artifacts.app_design}}",
    previous_feedback: "{{outputs.claude_review.summary}}",
    acceptance_criteria: "{{vars.acceptance_criteria}}"
  }

  ## 10. Contre-judge Codex -> done ou Paire 1
  counter_judge_codex -> done when ready

  counter_judge_codex -> claude_implement when not ready as impl_loop(6) with {
    design: "{{artifacts.app_design}}",
    previous_feedback: "{{outputs.claude_review.summary}}",
    acceptance_criteria: "{{vars.acceptance_criteria}}"
  }
